Important points:
Main issue: backend/server does not persist column role changes. App sends Admin/Manager, but server returns Supervisor.

Fix/workaround: save column role overrides in Project Preferences instead of relying on column DB role.

Preference key format requested by Kobayashi-san:

/ppiBreakdown/columnRoles/<root>/<role>
Example:
/ppiBreakdown/columnRoles/assets/manager
value: dev,testColumn001
Meaning: columns listed under that key require that role.

Files mainly changed:
state.py: reads/writes column role preferences.
columnManagerDialog.py: saves selected role to preferences.
mainWindow.py: applies saved role overrides when loading columns.
tableData.py: supports applying role override to Column.

UI message: should not mention server failure anymore. It should only say role will be saved in project preferences.

